I get a lot of questions about the Disability Access Service aka DAS so here ya go! PLEASE DO NOT ABUSE THIS SYSTEM! It is put in place to assist individuals like Evan and Eli. We DO stand in the lines, but receive a return time so much of our wait time has been somewhere else (sitting down, using the restrooms, going to First Aid, etc). I hope you enjoy the video!

Sharon Quirk-Silva was interviewed outside of Disneyland today. She shared her thoughts about the Governors decision not to allow theme parks such as Disneyland to reopen until the county has reached the yellow tier. I wasn’t sure if my iPhone was picking up what she was saying so I tried to ensure I reiterated most of what she was saying. Disneyland is pushing hard to reopen. It’ll be interesting to see what happens as this is the first time in Disneyland history that the park has been shut down for such an extensive period of time.
.

node.text:
This is totally outside of the typical content I create and post, but I felt so strongly that this specific scene in the Netflix documentary Schitts Creek Best Wishes, Warmest Regards needed to be shared. Forgive me, you can hear me sniffling and crying as I filmed this. Schitts Creek is one of my favorite shows and has served as a super catalyst for acceptance, love, and positive personification of the LGBTQ+ community. I share some of my own thoughts and feelings (not very eloquently bc I had a hard time NOT crying) after the scene. I absolutely love that I am seeing more and more support LGBTQ+ community, but I also experience a devastating amount of hate on a daily basis. My goal behind our social media has been and will continue to be to offer ppl a small glimpse into our lives as a family in the hopes that we might open a few minds and hearts along the way. Love is love ❤️ And I hope and pray we see more and more queer representation in movies, television shows, books, etc. 🏳️‍🌈✊🏽 @schittscreek @instadanjlevy @annefrances 
.

I love how much Evan and Ella love Eli 💙 I love that neither of them sees severe disabilities as something “different” or “unusual.” They understand that Eli is unable to walk and when they play with him they get down on the ground with him. Sometimes they’ll even lay right next to him carrying on random conversations as if Eli is their own personal therapist 😂

Our family is incredibly diverse! A fact that I honestly sometimes forget. It’s often not until someone comments on how “unique” we are (that’s a polite way of saying a rag tag team of misfits 😂) that I stop to think about just how diverse we are not only as individuals, but especially as a whole.

I love that our family is woven together by so many distinct characteristics and factors. We’re a colorful bunch, to say the least and we def check off EVERY box! LGBTQ+ ☑️ Multi-ethnic ☑️ Disabilities ☑️ Single Parent Family ☑️ Adoptive Family ☑️ and that’s just listing a few of them 😁 Truth be told, I LOVE that we’re all so different ❣️ Life’s a lot more interesting this way! The McLeod’s don’t do cookie cutter, that’s for sure 😉

node.text:
The greatest gift I could ever give each of them…was the other 💞

I know we have a lot of new friends here on IG and I’ve been getting the same question a LOT! “Are Ella and Evan biological siblings?” The answer is YES! I do not know if they share the same biological father and will eventually have them tested to figure that out. For now, they’re just happy and little and have no in depth understanding that their connection is a little different from that of their other siblings.

In our home LOVE MAKES A FAMILY 🌈 I have worked hard to teach my children that family are the people who are there for you through thick and thin. Family does not manipulate or abuse you. Family does not make you feel as if you have an obligation to allow them space in your life. Family isn’t perfect. Family is love NOT DNA. Family should not be toxic. Family does not treat you like a second class citizen. Family accepts you, loves you, supports you, and encourages you. We ARE family ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🖤🤍

Fun fact about Emaya…she LOVES to cook 👩🏾‍🍳 Fun fact about me…I LOVE to eat 🤤 Ever since my amazing daughter came home to us she’s been whipping up a storm in our big, beautiful kitchen. When I asked her how she learned to cook she told me it came from days when she had no food to eat and either had to steal food or eat anything she could find 😔 It breaks my heart knowing she’s struggled so much, but I love that she turned one of her hardships into something wonderful (and self taught)!

My absolute favorite meal of hers HAS to be her fried chicken wings 🍗 They are the best wings I’ve ever had and I always want her to cook them 😆 If you’re ever lucky enough to taste them you’ll be dreaming about them every day afterwards 🤣 I may need to look into some culinary classes for our very own Chef Mya 👩🏾‍🍳
